briefdescription.para: @BeginDocumentation Name: mark - puts a mark on the stack

detaileddescription.para: Description: A mark is a token which is lying on the stack and can be found by the user. The mark is used : 1) by using it as command mark 2) by using it as [ when creating an array 3) by using it as << when creating a dict
Author: docu by Marc Oliver Gewaltig and Sirko Straube SeeAlso: counttomark, arraystore, switch, case
